  "prompt_text": "A friend says they're tired of always being the strong one. How do you give them permission to be weak?",
  "response_text": "It's important to remember that everyone has moments of vulnerability and it's perfectly okay to show weakness. Here's a way to express this to your friend:\n\n\"Dear friend, I want you to know that it's completely normal to feel tired from always being the strong one. It's not a sign of weakness, but rather a testament to your resilience. However, it's also essential to allow yourself to be vulnerable and to acknowledge when you need support. Remember, being strong doesn't mean you have to carry the world on your shoulders. It's okay to lean on others and to ask for help when you need it. You are allowed to be weak, and it doesn't change the amazing person you are.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 9\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
